Videoez Backend — Video Upload & Streaming API

This repository contains the backend API for Videoez — a simple service that enables uploading, storing, and streaming video files. It is built using Node.js + Express with clean, modular architecture.

⸻

FEATURES
	•	Upload video files
	•	Store uploaded videos locally
	•	Fetch list of uploaded videos
	•	Stream videos using HTTP range requests
	•	Clear folder structure
	•	Centralized error handling
	•	CORS enabled

⸻

TECH STACK

Node.js
Express.js
Multer (file uploads)
fs / Streams (for video streaming)
dotenv
Nodemon

⸻

INSTALLATION & SETUP
	1.	Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/TalibYousuf/Videoez.git
cd Videoez
	2.	Install dependencies
npm install
	3.	Create a .env file in the root folder with the following:
PORT=5000
UPLOAD_DIR=uploads
	4.	Start the server
npm start

Server will run at:
http://localhost:5000

⸻

API ENDPOINTS
	1.	Upload Video
POST /api/videos/upload
Content-Type: multipart/form-data
Uploads a video file to the server.
	2.	Stream Video
GET /api/videos/stream/:filename
Streams a video using range-based streaming.
Works with HTML5 video players.
	3.	Get All Videos
GET /api/videos
Returns a list of uploaded video files.

⸻

FOLDER STRUCTURE

Videoez/
├── uploads/ (stored videos)
├── controllers/
├── routes/
├── middleware/
├── server.js
├── .env.example
└── README.md

